(3) An applicant who receives a notice under subsection (2) shall, within seven days of the receipt thereof, inform the local authority , in writing, that— (a) he agrees to the imposition of such conditions; or (b) that he does not so agree and that— (i) he intends to appeal under the provisions of section ten; or (ii) he abandons his application.
